Disjoint-support extrema
------------------------

The disjoint filter requires q and a to be absent from the background
word together with the appended plus leaf p.

Exact finite family:
  mode=finite k=3
  background=[2,2,...,2] (n copies)
  (p,q,a)=(2,1,1)
  R-|C|=1 for every n

Selected exact outputs:
  n=9:  |C|/R=12595/12596, gap=1
  n=10: |C|/R=40755/40756, gap=1
  n=11: |C|/R=131891/131892, gap=1
  n=12: |C|/R=426803/426804, gap=1

Ordinary maximum strict disjoint ratio in the declared n=9 batch:
  word=[2,2,2,2,2,2,4,4,4]
  (p,q,a)=(2,1,1)
  |C|/R=94356/97184
  gap=2828

There are also disjoint exact equalities |C|/R=1 on wall/support faces,
often with q=a.  The strict k=3 family proves that no uniform relative
gap below one is available even after the minimal-counterexample filter.

Sign conjecture falsification
-----------------------------

Smallest finite witness:
  mode=finite k=2
  background=[2]
  (p,q,a)=(2,1,1)
  C=1
  (p-a)C=1 > 0
  R=1
  gap=0

The same C=1 calculation holds in every finite level k>=2 and in the
ordinary ring.  Thus sign(C)=-sign(p-a) is false independently of the
oscillation inequality.

Replay:
  /tmp/search_su2_boundary_oscillation --replay finite 2 2 1 1 2

Expected:
  F_NONZERO (0,2)=1 (2,0)=1
  C_FIRST=1 C_SECOND=0 C=1 ABS_C=1
  RHS_TERMS B(q,1)=1
  RHS=1 GAP=0
  IDENTITY B_AFTER_P=2 RHS_PLUS_C=2 B_AFTER_A=0 RHS_MINUS_C=0
  SIGN_TEST (p-a)*C=1 result=FAIL
